<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=615&amp;p=5061#p5061</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=615&amp;p=5061#p5061"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[6502 Perfect Timing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=615&amp;p=5061#p5061"><![CDATA[
Interrupts are not handled until after an instruction has finished executing. NMI/IRQ during BRK is a special case because the 6502 handles interrupts by literally executing a BRK instruction with special flags active to specify which vector to load (and to push the 'B' flag in the proper state).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Fri Sep 30, 2005 2:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
